This package contains the source code for xllmnrd.

xllmnrd is an IPv6 LLMNR responder daemon for GNU/Linux operating systems,
which allows Microsoft Windows clients to get the IPv6 address of a GNU/Linux
server on the same local network _without any DNS configuration_.

xllmnrd is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify it under the
terms of the GNU General Public License.  You should have received a copy of
it as the file 'COPYING' in this directory.

# Installation

For generic installation instructions, read the file 'INSTALL' in this
directory.  If you are also planning to run the included test suite with GCC,
you will have to set the environment variable 'CXX' to 'g++ -std=gnu++11' or
'g++ -std=gnu++0x' before installation, depending on the compiler version.
